===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Perhaps a {{liushu|p|nocap=1}} of a crack in an {{w|oracle bone}}, used for divination in ancient China.

Officially adopted as the simplified form of {{zh-l|*蔔}} in the ''Chinese Character Simplification Scheme'' ({{lw|zh|pref=《|s:漢字簡化方案|漢字簡化方案|suf=》}}) in 1956.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=𠁡,𠁢}}
"Cracking" of a bone or tortoise shell in fire: "to divine by oracle bone" ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Compare {{cog|adl|-`buk||to burst}}, {{cog|adl|-`puk||to pop}}, {{cog|lus|puak||to explode; to burst}} (STEDT). 

